        FileScanner scan = new FileInputStream(directory); // Creating a Scan object for directory using fileinputstream which provides methods to read files, directories etc. Here we are creating instance of it with the current working Directory '.'  or based on your need you can provide any other location (like /home/user)
        	scanner = scan;  			//Assigning Scan object created for directory reading in file input stream and later use this to read files, directories etc. within our program using methods of FileInputStream class provided by java standard library  ie., isDirectory(), exists().....etc .    This allows us not only security but also performance enhancing feature as it reads all the data from one location at a time (lazy loading) rather than buffering them up in memory like other ways.
